    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS, RINGS AND SLEEVES - PISTONS AND RINGS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>PISTONS AND RINGS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
            <title>INSTALLATION</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the rings onto the pistons using a piston ring expander tool as follows: (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150654">6.54</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the rings in order.</para>
                    <seqlist style="arabic">
                        <item>
                            <para>Oil control ring</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>2nd compression ring</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Top compression ring</para>
                        </item>
                    </seqlist>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Identification marks must face up. (Top ring has UP-TOP. 2nd ring has UP-2ND).
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>The oil ring does
                                <emph type="underscr">NOT</emph>
                                have identification marks. There is no top or bottom, it may be installed in either
                                direction.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Stagger the ring gaps 120&#176; apart.</para>
                    <figure id="ef4150653" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg5752" filename="../figcg5/CG5752.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 6.53. Install Shim(s) Reassembly.</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef4150654" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg12129" filename="../figcg1/CG12129.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 6.54. Install Piston Rings.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble the piston and connecting rod as follows: Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_119.xml" xrefid="ef4150655">6.55</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Lubricate the connecting rod piston pin bushing with clean engine oil.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the retaining ring at one end of the piston pin bore.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Insert the connecting rod into the piston aligning bored holes of the rod and piston
                        (the short side of the split on the crank end of the rod is to be toward the side of the piston
                        marked
                        <emph type="bold">"CAMSIDE"</emph>).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Align the pin bores and insert the piston pin.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the second retaining ring.</para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Rod and cap matching numbers must be opposite the camside of the piston.</para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
